  "text": "Study subjects. The study design has been described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, newly diagnosed patients with histologically confirmed lung cancer were recruited at The University of Texas M. D. Anderson Cancer Center (Houston, TX). Controls without a prior history of cancer (except nonmelanoma skin cancer) were recruited from patients attending appointments for routine medical care at the Kelsey-Seybold Clinics, a large multispecialty physician practice in Houston. Controls were frequency matched to cases by age, sex, ethnicity, and smoking status (never, former, current). Questionnaire data included demographic characteristics, prior medical history, and family history of cancer in first-degree relatives. The present study includes only non-Hispanic Caucasians, the major racial/ ethnic subgroup of subjects, to control for genetic differences across racial/ ethnic populations [CITATION_2] .",
